        <title type="html"><![CDATA[A Passionate Love letter to an Abusive Game]]></title>
        <id>https://WakeTechBrandon.github.io/tech-portfolio/blog/2023/01/07/Overwatch-A-Passionate-Love-Letter-To-An-Abusive-Game.html</id>
        <link href="https://WakeTechBrandon.github.io/tech-portfolio/blog/2023/01/07/Overwatch-A-Passionate-Love-Letter-To-An-Abusive-Game.html"/>
        <updated>2023-01-07T06:00:00.000Z</updated>
        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[<h1><a class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" id="overwatch"></a><a href="#overwatch" aria-hidden="true" class="hash-link"><svg class="hash-link-icon" aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Overwatch</h1>
<p>Overwatch is a team-based hero-shooter that released as a skeleton of a game and has been gradually developed into a welcoming AAA title.
The artistic style of the game is spot-on beautiful, and the lore allows for diversity in the roster to the point of a grizzeled old military veteren playing alongside a tesla-toting Gorilla and a cyborg ninja.
In no other game before this would one even remotely imagine playing a First-Person game with this diverse a roster with unique abilities, sizes, weapons, and movement capabilities.
Who could possibly turn down an invitation into such an inviting world; featuring such intense and diverse gameplay?</p>
]]></summary>
